<br>
The forces of the Desert Fist were dispatched to Belis Corona three weeks ago to quell an uprising of traitorous guardsmen and technicians who were seeking to steal the vast Imperial munitions stored below the planet’s surface.  The hardened and twisted bodies of those gathered against them garnered the same protection as the modified power armor worn by the forces of the Desert Fist.  No other forces could stand to fight on the surface of this wasteland, let alone struggle for weeks on end.  Battles were started all over the planet, all the while driving the physically twisted mutants and mentally twisted traitors towards this central battleground in the deepest crater on Belis Corona.<br>
<br>
“Chaplain Rommel,” quietly started the frail Librarian Thomas Lawrence, “we have all but destroyed the traitors.  It is how you guessed, they will not surrender.  However, I fear the winds are changing and this is only the beginning of the Chaos insurgence.”<br>
<br>
Rommel sighed, “You are right Lawrence, I also feel the foul force upon the wind.  I believe our new orders should arrive soon, for we will be desperately needed closer to the Cadian system.  Whatever our orders may be, you must remain here, docked in the orbital shipyards.  The forces of the dark ones will not allow this position to function unhindered.  But most of all I fear the other forces of the desert; the Necrons will not sit idly by.  Whether they will fight beside us or against us, I do not know.  However, I cannot place any trust in them to remain away from this planet ripe for their picking.  You will remain here with enough men to hold this planet.  I trust your skills to fend off any hostile force and keep the men disciplined; we may need your help before this campaign is over.”<br>
